<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Charm Oddities</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=611425" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    This news is a few days old but better late then never.  The Developers Corner on the offical everquest website is reporting some issues with Charm abilities.  Check it out:<br>
<blockquote>
  <i>There is a way (which I'm not going to explain...) to make it look like your 
charms are gaining a lot of extra stats. If you see this happening, please do 
not think that your charm actually has those stats and run of thinking that you 
are now invincible. You're not. <BR><BR>This is a visual bug. The stat increase 
is only on your client, and is not seen nor accepted by our servers. It's not a 
super charm. <BR><BR>We'll fix this bug when we can. <BR><BR>Alan <BR></i>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=611425">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

		</table>

	</td>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
