				Len Thank you for one of the most intelligent responses I have heard in a long time.<BR>
<BR>
I agree with you perception is everything. <BR>
<BR>
I watched a multi-million dollar corporation almost go bankrupt because of poor customer service.<BR>
<BR>
They made a good technical product but with all technical products they have quirks.<BR>
<BR>
Word got out that they were being condescending and evasive with certain problems.<BR>
<BR>
Next thing you know their sales dropped 60% in one year because another competitor picked up on this fault and went overboard to be just the opposite.<BR>
<BR>
The company I work for now spends an average of 20 million dollars with the competitor, and none of us will touch the original company which had a good product.<BR>
<BR>
Bottom line: Perception is Everything!
