				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, Len, I'll give you major kudos for being more rational in your explanation this time.<BR>
<BR>
However, of course he's going to clarify exactly what can be done...just not the how.  Otherwise, he'd be inundated by people asking for clarification.  Happens all the time.<BR>
<BR>
The terminology is of a player to a player.  You may dislike it, or think it disparaging, however you are most likely in the minority.  He was blunt, because he has to be blunt.  Too many people need it that way.<BR>
<BR>
Sure, everything has a priority...this one happens to be extremely low.  The percentage of people that actually have a charm vs the ones that don't has got to be (yes, this is a guess) no more than 20% of all customers.  I'd even be willing to say half of that.<BR>
<BR>
They are too busy to fix this minor inconvenience. They are busy fixing other, more important bugs/problems.  It's a statement that, &quot;Yes&quot; they know about it and &quot;Yes&quot; it will be fixed.  However, they don't have an ETA on it as of yet.  Too many people blame them for being blind to the bugs in the game.  This counteracts that.<BR>
<BR>
Your opinion is valid, but in MY opinion, it's completely wrong.  Though, again, I'd like to say that you at least took the time to rationally explain your words.  That shows integrity.<BR>

